Package: readflex
Type: Package
Title: Flexible CSV reader with auto-detected encoding
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Toshihiro", "Iguchi",
      email = "toshihiro.iguchi.github@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: `readflex()` attempts to read a CSV file by automatically detecting its character encoding
    (using `readr::guess_encoding()` or `stringi::stri_enc_detect()`) and falls back to
    a user-specified list of common encodings if detection fails.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
  readr,
  stringi,
  utils
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
